Peacefully located on Rose Street in Tuyen Lam Lake tourist area, Dalat Wonder Resort stands out as the first choice for short or long vacation. In addition to the quality of attentive service and excellent products provided to the guests, the resort is surrounded by scenic spots and has many points to visit such as Truc Lam Zen Monastery, Van Hanh Zen Monastery, Prenn Waterfall, and Waterfall Pongour, Chicken Church, Cam Ly Waterfall, Nam Phuong Hoang Hau Palace, Tran Le Xuan Palace, XQ Historical Shop, Thanh That Cao Dai Dalat. Located along a branch of Tuyen Lam Lake, Dalat Wonder Resort is put into operation with 216 guestrooms, including 171 rooms in 19 villas and 45 rooms in the hotel building. Dalat Wonder Resort owns poetic scenery like a miniature "Europe" right in Dalat. The resort impresses visitors not only with the charming natural scenery but also with impressive European architecture and many amenities such as outdoor pool, garden and terrace. Aiming to become the first and unique resort - entertainment complex in Da Lat, we offer "All-IN-ONE" experiences to customers. It is a combination of the hotel, villas, conferences & events at Dalat Wonder Resort, the amusement park Wonderland featuring many attractive activities such as zoo, flower garden, yatch, sports, strawberry garden, herbal garden, etc. The perfect environment and atmosphere of the resort gives you a peaceful and relaxing holiday with favorable weather and the green landscape of "City of fog of thousands of flowers".

Nathan Pham wrote a review May 2019
Dong Nai Province, Vietnam
+ 1
Ideal for quiet person, service is so-so
Stay at resort for 2 nights, Premier Lake View room
1/ Pros: Beautiful view, suitable for treating yourselft with nature.
Location besides Tuyen Lam lake, there's no point that you can complain on the view.
Nice Infinity pool
Price is very good for traveler
2/ Cons: still has lots of cons
a/ Have no bath curtain for bathtube, result to flooded water on the floor after bath
b/ Have no doormat: I must use my towel to do doormat. minus point for this
b/ No razor (shave): when ask for razor, they said that they just provide when ask, not complimentary ??? why ? a 4-star resort cannot do that.
c/ Room is smaller than in photos, but it is ok with the price.
d/ Room has balcony, but it is a shared (public) balcony, not a private balcony. People from other room can break in my room if I dont lock the door. So, it is a big minus point. should separate the balcony of each room
e/ Infinity pool: the light of the pool in night is very disappointed. I cannot swim and take photo of the pool in night (before 8am). please study other resort with Infinity Pool to improve the pool (ie. Marinay Bay Sand in Singapore, or DaNang goldey bay in Viet Nam
f/ shuttle bus: very few shuttle bus, the last shuttle bus return resort is 9.30pm.. how come Resort should arrange bus like that ? Dalat is a tourrist destination, and i must return resort by 9:30pm ? Should arrange the last bus at 11:00pm.

Perfect resort in Dalat

The staff are attentive and always try to meet guest needs. Swimming pool is spacious, my kid loved it so much. The resort is quite far from the center (6-7km) but it is an ideal place for relaxing and finding some tranquil life, they also provide free shuttle bus to town and return 3 times per day. serjey wrote a review Mar 2019
Khimki, Russia
Не стоит своих денег
Отель расположен в живописном месте на озере, проживание в отдельных домиках. На первый взгляд все идеально: просторные номера с камином, терраса с видом на озеро, хороший ремонт. Но если присмотреться находишь много недочётов для отеля такого уровня: не работала горячая вода, слив в душе сделан так что весь пол заливает водой, отсутствует спорт зал, территория не до конца облагорожена, завтрак азиатский (тяжёлая острая пища). Отель в стадии строительства, тяжело найти место для хорошей прогулки.

LisiJa wrote a review Feb 2019
+ 1
Mangelhaft und keine 4 Sterne wert
- Das Hotel befindet sehr entlegen - gratis Shuttleservice gibt es. Jedoch sind die Zeiten für die Hin- und Rückfahrt unlogisch. Beispiel: 19.30 Uhr in die Stadt (Ankunft ca 20-25 Minuten später) - Rückfahrt 21.30 Uhr

- Anlage: noch nicht komplett fertig gestellt. Es befinden sich mehrere Baustellen dort.

- Pool zwar schön, aber sehr kalt.

- Zimmer: zwar geräumig, jedoch bildet sich bereits Schimmel im Badezimmer. In der Früh, befand sich an der großen Fensterfront überall Kondenswasser.
Die Zimmer sind generell sehr hellhörig.

- Essen und Service: Wir kamen im Hotel an und haben im Restaurant Platz genommen. Wir wurden nicht bedient, obwohl nur sehr wenige Gäste anwesend waren. Getränke mussten wir deshalb selbst organisieren. Abends wollten wir a la Carte Essen - im Zimmer haben wir gesehen, dass dies angeboten wird. An diesem Abend fand ein asiatisches Galamenü statt, welches wir nicht einnehmen wollten. Daher unsere Frage ob wir Spaghetti (wie in der Menükarte ersichtlich) bekommen würden. Nach einem Hin- und Her wurden diese uns serviert, wobei uns mitgeteilt wurde, dass wir nur ca. 40 Minuten Zeit fürs Essen haben würden. Danach würde das Galadinner beginnen. Wir wurden dabei wieder nicht gefragt, ob wir etwas trinken möchten. Somit nahmen wir unser Essen ohne Getränke zu uns. Ich finde das ganze unverständlich. Wir fühlten uns geduldet, jedoch nicht willkommen.

Das Frühstück ist eher auf Asiaten ausgelegt. "Leider" waren wir während des Tet-Festes dort, somit war auch reger Betrieb und man hatte eher das Gefühl einer Mensa, als in einem 4 Sterne Resort.

Ingesamt finde ich das Hotel überteuert, es ist eindeutig Luft nach oben. Auf den ersten Blick findet man es schön, bei genauerem Betrachten waren wir schnell frustriert.

r1gjwm wrote a review Dec 2018
Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
Wonderful
I come to stay at Tuyen Lam Lake area regularly & have stayed at many of the resorts in this area & I must say that even although building the resort is still work in progress I really loved staying here over Christmas, it was a Wonderful experience right enough. The setting beside the lake in the mountains is stunning. The staff were first class & so friendly. The Christmas Dinner was really good & well worth the 500k VND charge which included half a bottle of red wine. Before dinner on Christmas Eve a group of carol singers entertained the guests & they were fantastic & set the feeling for the night. All in all even although the resort is new & work on going it was a great holiday & when this resort is finished it will be the best resort on Tuyen Lam lake I think & great value for money. I will definitely return to this resort.
